h dandy, running up considerable tailor’s bills. Before his execution at age thirty-two, he played a decisive role in revolutionary politics and even governed France in 1791 through a secret correspondence with Marie-Antoinette. In the first biography for more than a century, John Hardman traces Barnave’s life from his youth in Dauphiné to his role in the Constituent Assembly and his part in forming the Feuillants, the party dedicated to the moderate cause. Despite his early death, Barnave left a remarkable volume of material, from published works to thousands of manuscript pages. Hardman uses this rich archive to explore the life of this elusive writer, politician, and thinker—and sheds new light on the revolutionary period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRevolutionarieszFrancevBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300272185?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300272185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300272185/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZD